<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/133000269/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """Progressive assessment:
This course is based on continuous assessment where students will have 3 individual presentations with a debate on the topic chosen by each student. The following items will be considered to evaluate these activities: the soundness of the scientific evidences that support the argumentation. Poster and oral expression. Clarity and originality in data presentation

Final examination (only for those choosing this option instead of the continuous assessment or failed in the progressive assessment):
The students will take a written exam. The quality of the written expression, the creativity, the knowledge and the soundness of the arguments used to answer essay questions will be taken into consideration."""@es ;
    ns1:hasEvaluationTrial <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/133000269/2025-26/evaluation/trial1>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/133000269/2025-26/evaluation/trial2>,
